    <h1>Multiplayer Online Battle Arena (MOBA): Teamwork and Glory</h1>
    
    <p>If traditional strategy games are about controlling the entire army, the Multiplayer Online Battle Arena (MOBA) genre is about zooming in and controlling a single, incredibly powerful hero. In a standard MOBA, two teams of five players clash on a symmetrical map. Your goal? Battle through defensive towers, AI-controlled minions, and enemy players to destroy the central structure inside the enemy base.</p>
    
    <h3>The Warcraft III Connection</h3>
    <p>The MOBA genre has a fascinating origin story: it wasn't created by a massive game studio, but by passionate fans! It started as a custom map called <em>Defense of the Ancients (DotA)</em>, built entirely within the map editor of <em>Warcraft III</em>. Players loved the focus on hero combat and teamwork so much that this simple mod eventually exploded into the most popular and competitive esports genre in the world.</p>

    <h3>Is this genre for you?</h3>
    <p>If you thrive on teamwork, fast reflexes, and deep character mastery, MOBAs are incredibly rewarding. You don't need to build bases or harvest wood; instead, you focus entirely on using your hero's unique abilities, buying the right items, and coordinating with your team to win massive, flashy team fights.</p>
    
    <h3>Must-Play Masterpieces</h3>
    
    <h4>1. League of Legends (LoL)</h4>
    <p>The undisputed titan of the genre. <em>League of Legends</em> took the original MOBA formula and streamlined it, making it more accessible while maintaining a massive skill ceiling. With well over a hundred unique "Champions" to choose from, fast-paced combat, and a global esports scene that fills real-world stadiums, it is a modern cultural phenomenon.</p>
    
    <img src="images/lol.jpg" alt="League of Legends epic team fight" class="page-image" />
    
    <h4>2. Dota 2</h4>
    <p>The direct, official sequel to the original <em>Warcraft III</em> mod. <em>Dota 2</em> is known for being the deeper, more complex older brother of the MOBA world. It features advanced mechanics like "denying" your own minions to prevent enemies from getting gold, using a courier to deliver items across the map, and incredibly powerful abilities that can completely wipe out an enemy team in seconds.</p>
    
    <img src="images/dota2.jpg" alt="Dota 2 glowing abilities and heroes" class="page-image" />

        <h3>Dive Deeper</h3>
    <p>Curious about how this genre evolved from a simple mod into a global esports phenomenon? <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multiplayer_online_battle_arena" target="_blank">Read more about the history and mechanics of MOBA games</a>.</p>
